            {
                "comment": "Steve is providing really great lecture and is really nice to talk to after class. He is really knowledgable and gives very great introduction to how optimization works. This is a class that you don't want to miss if you are interesting how optimization works. The project are in julia code, which is super nice to use.",
                "difficulty_rating": 4,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "If you just want to get an A in this course, then the difficulty of this course is 2-3, but the content and the topics of the lectures are more difficult than average. Those topics are insightful and will help you succeed in future CS learning (especially for algorithm and machine learning). Prof. Wright is very kind and generous in grading.",
                "difficulty_rating": 4,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "This class was so much more difficult than it needed to be. That being said, aside from general disorganization in lectures, he does a good job of presenting the material during lectures. My only qualm with this prof is that his grading criteria is very (and unnecessarily) harsh.",
                "difficulty_rating": 5,
                "quality_rating": 3
